<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>REPLY TO STATEMENT OF DEFENCE AND STATEMENT OF DEFENCE TO COUNTERCLAIM</UNDER></TI>
<P>1. The plaintiffs, defendants by counterclaim, repeat all allegations in their Statement of Claim and deny each and every allegation in the Statement of Defence and Counterclaim.</P>
<P>2. The plaintiffs specifically deny that the defendant Patrick Guilbert (hereinafter referred to as &ldquo;Patrick&rdquo;), had anything whatever to do with the setting of the fire and further deny that the fire was set at all, but was rather an accidental fire.</P>
<P>3. The plaintiffs state that at all times material hereto, the defendant was in possession of the Fire Commissioner's report, and has no information to the contrary about the cause of the fire. Its allegations of arson are thus unfounded, malicious and designed to cause harm financially, and otherwise, to the plaintiffs.</P>
<P>4. The plaintiffs state further that it was known to the defendant that the fire, more likely than not, started during the afternoon, when smoke was detected by smell, by employees of the plaintiffs.</P>
<P>5. Contrary therefore, to the allegations of the defendant, Patrick did not have exclusive opportunity to set a fire, and this was specifically known by the defendants; however, it is denied that the fire was anything but an accidental electrical fire.</P>
<P>6. Further, the apartments upstairs were all occupied, giving additional proof of the absence of exclusivity of Patrick, a fact not only known by the defendant, but referenced in the Statement of Defence. Additionally, the condominiums were only days from being converted so that they could be sold, prior to which they were not available for sale, contrary to the allegations in the Statement of Defence.</P>
<P>7. The plaintiffs state that they were and are desirous of replacing the building and are only unable to do such due to the contractual breach and tortious actions of the defendant. Discussions were underway to replace the building until the defendant indicated its refusal to honour the policy.</P></BLOCK1>
<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I"><UNDER>STATEMENT OF DEFENCE TO THE COUNTERCLAIM</UNDER></TI>
<P>8. The plaintiffs, defendants by Counterclaim, repeat all the allegations above.</P>
<P>9. The plaintiffs deny any wrongdoing by them and state they are entitled to the relief pleaded for in the Statement of Claim, and not liable to the Defendant, Plaintiff by Counterclaim, for any of the matters claimed by it.</P>
<P>10. The plaintiffs, defendant by Counterclaim, deny the entitlement, in any event, of those matters referred to in paragraph 15(b) through 15(f) as being remote and unnecessary.</P>
<P>11. The plaintiffs, defendant by Counterclaim, therefore submit that the Counterclaim he dismissed with costs on a solicitor and own client basis.</P>
<P>Date: November &ellip10;, 2015.</P>
